🐰💙 

We’re delighted that China no longer requires animal testing for imported ordinary cosmetic products. 

The move marks an important milestone on the journey to a global ban on animal testing for cosmetics. But a change to long-standing legislation in Europe puts this at risk. 

The European Chemicals Agency, @EU_ECHA, is calling for new animal testing on ingredients that have been safely used for years. We want the EU’s ban on animal testing for cosmetics to be upheld, sparing the lives of millions of animals that will otherwise be used unnecessarily. 

We know science provides more reliable and far more humane ways to assess product safety. Unilever is recognised by @PETA as a company working for regulatory change and we have been using non-animal methods and sharing our research in this area for many years. 

We’ve come too far to go back now. We say #UseScienceNotAnimals. Do you? 

#EndAnimalTesting #YesToPositiveBeauty
